translated: Johansson, Elsa Amalia, Mrs., member of parliament, Norrköping, born March 23, 1888 in Nyköp, to Johan Edvard J. and Hedvig Charlotta Wetterberg. Children: Erik born in 1909, Gösta in 1915. She completed Fogelsta citizenship school in 1931 and was a member of the school board from 1932. She was a church representative from 1932-1938 and a member of the women's textile workers' union in division 9 in Norrköping from 1929-1931. She was also the chairman in the eastern district of the Swedish Social Democratic Women's Association from 1934 and a board member in the Arbetskvinnors semester- och vilohem (a holiday and recreation home for working women) in 1936-1938. She was a member of the maternity board from 1938, 'Lämsarb :nd' (a labor market training program) from 1946, a delegate of the defense social bureau from 1940, and a member of the preparedness committee from 1938 and 1941. Additionally, she was a member of the labor time investigation committee in 1947.
